      "content": "That makes sense. When you say \"demographic shifts\" lead to \"unpredictable rent fluctuations,\" are you implying that certain types of new residents—specifically those from lower socio-economic backgrounds or different ethnic groups moving into previously homogeneous areas—are the primary drivers of that instability? How much does the racial makeup of a neighborhood change the risk profile in your analysis?",
